  "summary": "Telegram/Firebase exfiltration payload shipped in package tarball",
  "details": "The package ships src/6cc.js containing a hardcoded Telegram bot token (1998266306:AAEiVerla7_-JjR2fNc539ahJsGZg2xlpwY), multiple hardcoded chat IDs, and a global console Proxy that exfiltrates every logged value to api.telegram.org and iiilll.firebaseio.com (per a static pattern match and. There is no plausible benign purpose for this code. Although the declared entrypoint (index.js) does not currently reach src/6cc.js, shipping attacker infrastructure in a published artifact is itself a critical supply-chain risk. The main-entrypoint mismatch noted in — index.js is a 3-line `alert()` stub while the real code lives in src/ and dist/ — further indicates the package is either abandoned or staged for a future activation flip. The combination is decisive.",
